Recommended Steps to Fix:
Step 1: Use a Virtual Environment (Highly Recommended)
This avoids "site-packages is not writeable" errors and keeps your global Python clean.

powershell
# Create venv
python -m venv venv
# Activate venv
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1




Step 2: Install Updated Requirements

powershell
pip install -r requirements.txt




Step 3: Run Locally on Windows
Use a hardcoded port (like 8000) for local testing:

powershell
uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload
Note on Render Deployment
When you deploy to Render, the command uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT will work because Render automatically sets the $PORT environment variable. For local development, just use 8000.
